Female. First four segments of front tarsus only slightly dilated, subbilobed, each with tenent setae ventrally; segment two narrower than apex of tibia (ratio 0.83); tergite 10 of genital segment of characteristic shape, slightly pigmented medioapically, with several setae of unequal length at and near apex (
Fig.16
), or with two long, strong medial setae and two much shorter and finer setae at apex (
Fig.17
), otherwise asetose.
